Program: Discovery
Title: Malaria - the disease that refuses to die out
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxhv
Last Broadcast Date: 15 October 1999
Is the eradication of malaria possible? It causes two million deaths in Africa alone and many people in the continent spend large proportions of their income on ways of preventing infection, many proving ineffective. Despite being almost partly eradicated in the 1950s resistance against medication has grown amid growing concern. Show less